de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.fusion.areal

Class ArealClusteringObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.fusion.clustering.ClusteringObject
      • de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.fusion.areal.ArealClusteringObject

  • public class ArealClusteringObject
extends ClusteringObject
    This class is a subclass of ClusteringObject. It overrides the methods to calculate a distance to another ClusteringObject and the core distance.
    Since:
    24.02.2014
    Author:
    Sebastian Schulz

      • setCoreDistance

        public void setCoreDistance(int minNeighbors)
        This method overrides the ClusteringObject#setCoreDistance(TreeSet, int) method. It calculates the distance of the minNeighbors's neighbor and sets this value for coreDistance.
        Specified by:
        setCoreDistance in class ClusteringObject
        Parameters:
        minNeighbors - - an int value which represents the minimal count of neighbors for the object to be a core object.

      • getDistance

        public double getDistance(ClusteringObject destinationObject)
        This method overrides the ClusteringObject.getDistance(ClusteringObject) method. And returns the euclidean distance between the geographic coordinates of both objects.
        Specified by:
        getDistance in class ClusteringObject
        Parameters:
        destinationObject - - a arbitrary ClusteringObject.
        Returns:
        the distance as an double value.
